 Silulumanzi have issued an announcement about water service disruption due to a burst on the pump line to KaNyamazane from the Water Treatment Works plant. “Technicians have already started with repairs and it is estimated that it will take about four hours to complete. Water supply to KaNyamazane will be affected from tonight until Wednesday morning. We will keep you updated of developments.” They have urged customers to use water sparingly and have apologized for any inconveniences that this might cause. They have also asked the public to report any water interruptions to 086-174-5858. After hours standby can also be reached at the same number with any enquiry or emergency during non-working periods. ALSO READ: Police to investigate bomb scare at station